==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nonchalant
<hw>Non`cha`lant"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>non</ets> not (L. <ets>non</ets>) + <ets>chaloir</ets> to concern
one's self for, fr. L. <ets>calere</ets> to be warm, to be inflamed with
desire, to be troubled. See <er>Non-</er>, and <er>Caldron</er>.]</ety>
<def>Indifferent; careless; cool.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nonchalantly</ent>⟦br⟧
